box-shadow: inset 0px 0x 0px 0px rgba(0,0,0, .25);

can place shadows inside of the element
1st number is the horizontal offset
2nd number is the vertical offset
3rd number is the blur-radius(size of blur)(big number will make the shadow appear softer)
		-does not accept negative values
4th number is the spread
	-spreading the shadow
	-can take negative numbers
the last number in the rgba value is opacity




ex: 
   box-shadow: 0px 20px;

the shadow will appear on the bottom
